I want to use getRandomObject() in cocos2d::Vector class.
It works well on win32-platform, but the same code doesn't work in android-platform.
so I track my class's member methods. And figure out rand() function cause this problem.

getRandomObject function in CCVector is:

T getRandomObject() const
    {
        if (!_data.empty())
        {
            ssize_t randIdx = rand() % _data.size();
            return *(_data.begin() + randIdx);
        }
        return nullptr;
    }

In addition, it can be caused that it would be non-complete random object.

so I recommend to change a function with using a RandomHelper class in cocos2d-x

or using a uniform_real_distribution in std namespace.

like this:

T getRandomObject() const
    {
        if (!_data.empty())
        {
            ssize_t randIdx = RandomHelper:: random_int(0,_data.size());
            return *(_data.begin() + randIdx);
        }
        return nullptr;
